WEBVTT

00:00.107 --> 00:01.835
<i>Previously on "Shades of Blue"...</i>

00:01.859 --> 00:04.227
Wozniak's convinced that
Saperstein's the mole.

00:04.252 --> 00:05.878
Whoa!

00:05.912 --> 00:07.413
Your secrets have poisoned you.

00:07.447 --> 00:09.515
But soon I'm gonna heal you.

00:09.549 --> 00:13.385
My daughter killed herself
right after we had a fight.

00:13.420 --> 00:14.790
Annie?

00:14.815 --> 00:17.890
And I've been trying to fill
the hole ever since.

00:17.924 --> 00:19.425
Does this guy look familiar to you?

00:19.459 --> 00:20.926
Yeah.

00:20.951 --> 00:22.379
Wallace just put intelligence
at the scene.

00:22.404 --> 00:24.363
Harlee was obsessed with Agent Stahl.

00:24.397 --> 00:25.531
<i>She's dangerous.</i>

00:25.565 --> 00:27.032
You're gonna need a second career

00:27.067 --> 00:27.966
when you realize who I am.

00:28.001 --> 00:30.202
What hooks do you have in Captain Ramsey?

00:30.236 --> 00:33.072
Enrique Ortiz is the son of the head

00:33.106 --> 00:35.441
of the Riohacha cartel.

00:35.475 --> 00:36.842
<i>He ordered a hit.</i>

00:38.578 --> 00:40.145
<i>That means the Riohacha cartel
is in bed with intelligence.</i>

00:40.180 --> 00:42.047
I can't follow him blindly.

00:42.082 --> 00:43.949
Not anymore.

00:43.983 --> 00:46.051
<i>Cops investigating cops
is dangerous business.</i>

00:46.086 --> 00:49.054
Going against their blue wall
is a lonely path.

00:49.089 --> 00:51.223
Was Bennett ordered to kill James Nava?

00:51.257 --> 00:53.158
I think he improvised.

00:53.193 --> 00:54.993
You're gonna break the blue wall

00:55.028 --> 00:57.162
against the intelligence division.

00:57.197 --> 00:58.497
Theo Bennett, you're under arrest

00:58.531 --> 01:00.232
for the murder of James Nava.

01:00.266 --> 01:01.967
<i>Do you understand your situation?</i>

01:02.001 --> 01:06.690
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

01:08.000 --> 01:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:19.152 --> 01:21.320
Sarcasm isn't the way
to go here, Lieutenant.

01:21.354 --> 01:23.355
This isn't sarcasm.

01:23.389 --> 01:24.456
It's contempt.

01:24.787 --> 01:28.127
Arresting an intelligence
officer outside my approval

01:28.161 --> 01:31.363
demonstrates a reckless
disregard for every honest cop

01:31.397 --> 01:32.598
in this precinct.

01:32.632 --> 01:34.433
No one's above the law.

01:34.467 --> 01:37.269
Internal Affairs should have
been your first call

01:37.303 --> 01:39.271
if you had concerns
within the department.

01:39.305 --> 01:42.274
They exist specifically
to avoid Blue-on-Blue

01:42.308 --> 01:43.275
conflicts of interest.

01:43.309 --> 01:45.978
I approached Detective Verco
about my concerns.

01:46.012 --> 01:47.379
Whoa, hold on, Detective.

01:47.413 --> 01:49.548
You floated a few rumors,
but you never objected

01:49.582 --> 01:52.284
to my closing the Sunrise file
when the guy that you shot

01:52.318 --> 01:54.987
was confirmed by ballistics
as the killer.

01:55.021 --> 01:57.489
I didn't arrest Theo Bennett
for the Sunrise.

01:57.524 --> 01:59.525
He murdered an assistant
District Attorney.

01:59.559 --> 02:01.209
So you're avenging your boyfriend?

02:01.243 --> 02:02.327
Is that it?

02:02.352 --> 02:04.496
Is that a Jordan Ramsey talking point?

02:04.521 --> 02:06.498
Yes, Lieutenant.
I spoke to Captain Ramsey,

02:06.523 --> 02:08.467
the head of our Intelligence service.

02:08.491 --> 02:10.602
He was curious if our little search party

02:10.627 --> 02:13.305
at his officer's apartment
found even a trace

02:13.339 --> 02:15.240
of the evidence you suggested.

02:15.275 --> 02:16.542
The evidence was there yesterday.

02:16.576 --> 02:19.144
So you obviously conducted
an illegal search.

02:19.179 --> 02:21.380
I thought a warrant would tip them off.

02:21.414 --> 02:23.015
And I was right.

02:23.783 --> 02:25.551
I'm releasing this peace officer.

02:25.585 --> 02:27.319
I see no evidence for his arrest,

02:27.353 --> 02:29.388
and frankly, you've pissed me off.

02:29.422 --> 02:31.390
Don't expect me to shield you
from the blowback.

02:31.424 --> 02:33.225
You go rogue, you go alone.

02:33.259 --> 02:35.327
- I can prove this.
- Then do it.

02:36.396 --> 02:38.363
He's already been arrested.

02:38.398 --> 02:40.232
Technically he's on a 24-hour
hold until I run

02:40.266 --> 02:41.233
and clear the paperwork.

02:41.267 --> 02:42.434
New evidence comes to light,

02:42.468 --> 02:44.036
internal affairs will look at it.

02:46.139 --> 02:47.567
Fine.

02:48.107 --> 02:50.542
If IA wants him, he's all yours.

02:50.577 --> 02:52.344
But he doesn't get booked
in this precinct.

02:52.378 --> 02:55.147
You're a real profile
of courage, aren't you?

02:57.550 --> 03:01.119
Intelligence is also
protecting Enrique Ortiz,

03:01.154 --> 03:03.355
so unimportant that
a Federal task force came

03:03.389 --> 03:04.590
and swooped him from our custody.

03:04.624 --> 03:06.058
They're not doing a very good job

03:06.092 --> 03:07.879
of protecting him, are they?

03:08.628 --> 03:10.596
So, what now, detectives?

03:10.630 --> 03:13.632
How do I help facilitate
the wild irony of you two

03:13.666 --> 03:15.367
investigating a cop for being dirty?

03:15.401 --> 03:17.269
[LAUGHS]

03:17.303 --> 03:19.438
Why don't you prep Bennett
for interrogation?

03:19.472 --> 03:20.642
As you wish.

03:21.307 --> 03:22.477
Verco.

03:23.309 --> 03:24.604
Thank you.

03:25.445 --> 03:27.479
Prepare to be unpopular, detectives.

03:27.513 --> 03:29.448
It's not as much fun as I make it look.

03:32.285 --> 03:36.455
We got 24 hours to charge this scarecrow.

03:36.489 --> 03:38.223
You got a plan?

03:38.258 --> 03:39.491
Did you read his military record?

03:39.525 --> 03:41.226
Yeah, he doesn't talk much.

03:41.261 --> 03:43.228
But maybe if we shake him up...

03:43.263 --> 03:45.631
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

03:45.665 --> 03:48.734
Woz, thank you for sticking by me today.

03:48.768 --> 03:51.136
I know you didn't wanna do it like this.

03:51.170 --> 03:52.404
<i>♪ </i>

03:52.438 --> 03:55.385
Even when you act alone, Harlee,

03:56.276 --> 03:58.243
you never act alone.

03:58.278 --> 03:59.645
<i>♪ </i>

03:59.679 --> 04:00.679
Matthews and Avery.

04:00.713 --> 04:02.180
- Right here, Captain.
- Here.

04:02.215 --> 04:03.348
Edgeworth and Schaefer.

04:03.383 --> 04:04.616
It's gonna be tough today.

04:04.651 --> 04:06.652
Yeah, price of Harlee starting a war.

04:06.686 --> 04:09.187
Soldiers on the front lines
get it the worst.

04:09.222 --> 04:10.522
Yeah, except I don't
remember volunteering.

04:10.556 --> 04:11.523
Brewster and Capriccio.

04:11.557 --> 04:12.524
- Here.
- Here.

04:12.558 --> 04:13.550
Donnelly and Stone.

04:13.584 --> 04:15.327
Alive and well, Drill Sergeant.

04:15.361 --> 04:16.595
Okay, priorities.

04:16.629 --> 04:18.430
The string of break-ins
on Bedford last week

04:18.464 --> 04:20.332
is starting to look connected,
so dig deep.

04:20.366 --> 04:21.565
Tufo and Nazario.

04:24.470 --> 04:25.671
You skipped us.

04:25.705 --> 04:27.834
- Did I?
- Uh-huh.

04:28.708 --> 04:30.142
My mistake.

04:30.877 --> 04:32.311
All right, let's get out there, people.

04:32.345 --> 04:34.279
I want double digits in holding by noon.

04:36.215 --> 04:37.683
Try to keep it to criminals today.

04:37.717 --> 04:39.451
If they got a badge, stay clear.

04:39.485 --> 04:40.752
Remind your curvy friend upstairs.

04:40.777 --> 04:43.288
How about I remind you that
she's upstairs for a reason?

04:43.313 --> 04:45.900
Oh, I got a few ideas as to
what those reasons could be.

04:45.934 --> 04:47.559
Ain't loyalty that got her to the top.

04:47.593 --> 04:49.528
I think you wanna hush up now, Donnelly.

04:49.562 --> 04:51.630
There's a whole city out there, Tufo.

04:51.664 --> 04:53.849
You sure you wanna keep making
enemies in here?

04:53.883 --> 04:55.634
Less traffic.

04:55.668 --> 04:57.369
Less warning.

04:57.403 --> 04:59.538
Okay, let's find an exit. Come on.

05:01.778 --> 05:02.903
What did I tell you?

05:02.938 --> 05:04.313
Harlee makes an impulsive decision,

05:04.347 --> 05:05.347
we all suffer the blow back.

05:05.382 --> 05:06.482
What else is new?

05:06.507 --> 05:09.251
Right now, I just wanna keep
my brother out of its way.

05:09.286 --> 05:11.487
Loman, tell me this is good news.

05:11.521 --> 05:13.022
[SIGHS]

05:20.363 --> 05:22.639
You still hear them, don't you?

05:23.266 --> 05:25.401
The voices that don't go quiet.

05:25.435 --> 05:28.170
They've been chasing you for years.

05:28.205 --> 05:29.371
Haven't they?

05:29.406 --> 05:32.190
Captains, Lieutenants, Sergeants.

05:33.076 --> 05:34.243
Dad.

05:34.277 --> 05:36.579
I'm exercising my right to silence.

05:36.613 --> 05:38.614
Have the nightmares stopped yet?

05:38.648 --> 05:41.116
<i>[SOFT, TENSE MUSIC]</i>

05:41.151 --> 05:44.253
It says here in your file that
you were at Kamdesh

05:44.287 --> 05:46.455
in Afghanistan.

05:46.489 --> 05:50.359
And then after that,
your service record goes dark.

05:50.393 --> 05:51.327
<i>♪ </i>

05:51.352 --> 05:54.597
What were you doing?
Jerking off in a tent?

05:54.631 --> 05:57.199
Did you lose any friends over there?

05:57.234 --> 05:58.367
Kill any civilians?

05:58.401 --> 05:59.843
I...

06:01.238 --> 06:05.407
I am exercising my right to silence.

06:05.442 --> 06:07.184
I get it.

06:07.944 --> 06:10.604
I packed body bags too.

06:11.448 --> 06:13.607
You made choices,

06:14.251 --> 06:16.026
and you survived.

06:16.753 --> 06:19.905
Even if you lost what made you human.

06:20.817 --> 06:22.751
I'm exercising my right to silence.

06:22.785 --> 06:24.393
Do you ever think about them?

06:24.427 --> 06:26.428
<i>♪ </i>

06:26.463 --> 06:28.867
The waitress who was trying
to make it home for some rest

06:28.901 --> 06:30.232
before the breakfast rush.

06:30.267 --> 06:32.401
<i>♪ </i>

06:32.435 --> 06:34.603
Is she any different than
the women and children

06:34.638 --> 06:36.639
from those torn down villages

06:36.673 --> 06:39.141
who were looking to you for help?

06:39.175 --> 06:41.410
Do you remember the moment

06:41.444 --> 06:43.646
they realized that you weren't
there to help them?

06:43.680 --> 06:46.792
<i>♪ </i>

06:46.817 --> 06:48.117
Like I said.

06:48.151 --> 06:50.653
<i>♪ </i>

06:50.687 --> 06:53.122
Have the nightmares stopped yet?

06:53.156 --> 06:58.427
<i>♪ </i>

06:58.461 --> 07:00.737
- I'm exercising...
- I know.

07:01.698 --> 07:03.432
I know your answer.

07:03.466 --> 07:04.633
<i>♪ </i>

07:04.668 --> 07:06.168
It's mine too.

07:06.202 --> 07:08.671
<i>♪ </i>

07:08.705 --> 07:11.440
Did you intercept James Nava that night

07:11.474 --> 07:13.208
with orders to kill him?

07:13.243 --> 07:16.679
<i>♪ </i>

07:16.713 --> 07:18.213
They're keeping his transfer
off the books.

07:18.248 --> 07:20.149
Oh, yeah? Who'd you have
to charm to get that deal?

07:20.174 --> 07:21.835
50-year-old gentleman named Carl.

07:21.869 --> 07:23.142
You should have sent me.

07:23.176 --> 07:24.701
Uh, I'm not sure, actually.

07:24.735 --> 07:26.288
All right, man. Wallace, you good?

07:26.323 --> 07:28.557
Yeah, now that you're here.

07:28.591 --> 07:30.178
- Oh, my man.
- Not you.

07:30.212 --> 07:31.213
Easy, sailor.

07:31.238 --> 07:33.295
Wouldn't want your heart rate to spike.

07:33.330 --> 07:34.630
[LAUGHS]

07:34.664 --> 07:36.498
Yo, Loman.

07:36.533 --> 07:38.567
You made sure the transfer
order is under an alias, right?

07:38.601 --> 07:40.235
Yeah, I wrote it up as a discharge.

07:40.270 --> 07:41.303
Different name, different hospital.

07:41.338 --> 07:42.371
He's safe.

07:42.396 --> 07:43.706
He can identify a cop in a mass murder.

07:43.731 --> 07:45.474
We're taking chances just being outside.

07:45.508 --> 07:46.475
Yeah.

07:46.509 --> 07:48.711
[TIRES SQUEALING]

07:48.745 --> 07:50.346
Tess, Tess, close those doors!

07:50.380 --> 07:51.313
Get back inside!

07:51.348 --> 07:53.382
Sir, put your hands where I can see them.

07:53.416 --> 07:54.383
[GUN COCKING]

07:54.417 --> 07:55.384
Don't do that, sir.

07:55.418 --> 07:56.585
Hands!

07:56.619 --> 07:57.586
- It's a gun!
- No, no, no, no!

07:57.620 --> 07:58.587
[GUN FIRES]

07:58.621 --> 08:00.214
It wasn't a gun, man!

08:00.248 --> 08:01.490
Chill!

08:01.524 --> 08:04.493
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

08:04.527 --> 08:05.461
<i>♪ </i>

08:05.486 --> 08:06.820
Yo, why didn't you listen to me, huh?

08:06.845 --> 08:08.230
You almost got yourself shot.

08:08.264 --> 08:15.571
<i>♪ </i>

08:20.764 --> 08:25.367
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

08:27.470 --> 08:29.237
<i>Is he talking yet?</i>

08:29.271 --> 08:31.573
More than he thinks he is.

08:31.607 --> 08:33.607
You and detective Santos
broke a cardinal rule.

08:33.642 --> 08:36.277
<i>I can list a few rules you're breaking.</i>

08:36.312 --> 08:38.513
I guess we all draw our own lines.

08:38.547 --> 08:40.148
I was laboring under the misapprehension

08:40.182 --> 08:41.352
that we have an agreement.

08:41.378 --> 08:43.590
There's breathing exercises for that.

08:43.615 --> 08:45.520
<i>Now that it's clear that we don't,</i>

08:45.554 --> 08:47.188
I'm gonna make you famous.

08:47.223 --> 08:50.258
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

08:50.292 --> 08:53.261
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

08:53.295 --> 08:55.296
<i>♪ </i>

08:55.331 --> 08:58.466
I'll endeavor to keep this short.

08:58.501 --> 08:59.570
Hey, Lieutenant.

08:59.605 --> 09:01.169
You're gonna want to see this.

09:01.194 --> 09:04.172
<i>The brave men and women
of NYPD's intelligence unit</i>

09:04.197 --> 09:07.208
<i>have been working for
four years to infiltrate</i>

09:07.243 --> 09:09.699
<i>and disarm this terrorist cell.</i>

09:10.379 --> 09:13.181
<i>We have diffused undetonated
explosive devices</i>

09:13.215 --> 09:14.405
<i>in three locations.</i>

09:14.439 --> 09:17.619
Detective Bennett himself
located two pipe bombs

09:17.653 --> 09:20.321
<i>near a subway station in Brooklyn.</i>

09:20.356 --> 09:23.558
<i>Unfortunately due to
a lack of the brotherhood</i>

09:23.592 --> 09:26.728
and the solidarity that
the NYPD is known for,

09:26.762 --> 09:29.831
Detective Bennett has now been
falsely accused

09:29.865 --> 09:32.539
and wrongfully detained by detectives

09:32.574 --> 09:34.335
<i>of the 64th precinct.</i>

09:34.370 --> 09:36.471
<i>The reckless behavior
they have demonstrated</i>

09:36.505 --> 09:39.207
<i>- has further compromised...
- [CLICKS]</i>

09:39.241 --> 09:40.408
Seriously?

09:40.443 --> 09:42.510
The anti-terrorism card?

09:42.545 --> 09:45.246
Nobody fact checks the boogeyman.

09:45.281 --> 09:50.218
<i>♪ </i>

09:50.252 --> 09:52.654
You had to expect that they
were gonna strike back.

09:52.688 --> 09:54.355
We can't let them canonize this guy.

09:54.390 --> 09:56.424
Well, if Bennett's not gonna talk,

09:56.459 --> 09:57.759
then we're gonna have to plant.

09:57.793 --> 09:59.227
No, nothing dirty!

09:59.261 --> 10:00.428
With Ramsey, it's gotta be straight,

10:00.463 --> 10:01.448
or we don't do it.

10:01.473 --> 10:03.665
Don't do it? We're already in it!

10:03.699 --> 10:05.567
You said that there was evidence.

10:05.601 --> 10:07.435
Nava's notebook.

10:07.470 --> 10:09.671
So we replace it with something else.

10:09.705 --> 10:11.706
We call in a favor to Gail Baker.

10:11.740 --> 10:14.542
Maybe she can get me access to Enrique.

10:14.577 --> 10:16.678
The cartel is Ramsey's soft spot.

10:16.712 --> 10:20.682
I think she holds the IOUs
in our relationship.

10:20.716 --> 10:22.617
We can take a stand.

10:22.651 --> 10:25.787
Here. Refuse to sink to their level.

10:25.821 --> 10:28.556
Harlee, you just thanked me
for standing with you

10:28.591 --> 10:30.558
when you made this arrest.

10:30.593 --> 10:33.695
That I knew was gonna start a war.

10:33.729 --> 10:36.698
The entire department
could turn against us.

10:36.732 --> 10:39.701
Don't tie my hands behind my back now.

10:39.735 --> 10:40.869
Not now.

10:40.903 --> 10:43.805
<i>♪ </i>

10:43.839 --> 10:47.575
Woz, this is when our
choices matter the most.

10:47.610 --> 10:49.711
When what's wrong is easy...

10:49.745 --> 10:50.999
This is not easy.

10:51.024 --> 10:52.881
And what's right is full of danger,

10:52.915 --> 10:55.550
that's when we decide who we are.

10:55.584 --> 10:58.720
I'm just trying to keep us alive.

10:58.754 --> 11:02.290
I'm sorry if it's not
righteous enough for you.

11:02.324 --> 11:03.591
You know, maybe I should have
just put a bullet

11:03.626 --> 11:04.736
in Bennett's head.

11:04.770 --> 11:08.429
Ah, now that's a constructive suggestion!

11:08.464 --> 11:10.431
We got 22 hours.

11:10.466 --> 11:12.600
The first 11, we'll do it your way.

11:12.635 --> 11:14.636
After that, it's my way.

11:14.670 --> 11:17.839
<i>♪ </i>

11:17.873 --> 11:21.576
[EMERGENCY SIRENS WAILING]

11:21.610 --> 11:24.846
Paramedics said the guy
had a fever of 103.

11:24.880 --> 11:26.447
Never should have been driving.

11:30.819 --> 11:32.587
Look, I'll type up the accidental weapon

11:32.621 --> 11:34.455
discharge report.

11:34.490 --> 11:35.857
Last minute you saw it wasn't a gun,

11:35.891 --> 11:37.458
fired into the ground.

11:37.493 --> 11:38.793
No injured civilians.

11:38.827 --> 11:40.628
At the last minute, hmm?

11:40.663 --> 11:41.829
Look, man, I get it, all right?

11:41.864 --> 11:44.332
Intelligence, sicarios...

11:44.366 --> 11:45.934
I'm nervous too.

11:45.968 --> 11:47.502
But I know what it's like
to shoot an unarmed man,

11:47.536 --> 11:48.670
and I wanted to spare you.

11:48.695 --> 11:50.405
Yeah, you almost spared me
my life, Loman.

11:50.430 --> 11:51.849
Tufo, I knew he didn't have a gun.

11:51.874 --> 11:53.196
I did not.

11:53.809 --> 11:55.443
All we can do is make decisions

11:55.477 --> 11:56.945
based on the information that we have.

11:56.979 --> 11:58.680
And I had more information than you.

11:58.714 --> 11:59.814
Well, wouldn't that be nice?

11:59.848 --> 12:00.915
[SCOFFS]

12:01.287 --> 12:03.551
If we could always react
to things exactly as they are?

12:03.586 --> 12:04.799
Why shouldn't we?

12:04.824 --> 12:06.354
Because in the real world,
people shoot at you

12:06.379 --> 12:07.622
for no reason, Loman.

12:07.647 --> 12:10.255
Because they're on meth.
Because you're wearing blue.

12:10.826 --> 12:13.661
And we're not even safe
in our own precinct anymore.

12:13.696 --> 12:15.663
And if that guy back there
pulled out a gun

12:15.698 --> 12:17.966
instead of a phone and we
waited until we knew,

12:18.000 --> 12:19.000
it'd be too late.

12:20.869 --> 12:22.904
Get a nice memorial service
out of it, though.

12:22.938 --> 12:25.006
I'd rather have a nice
service for the right reasons

12:25.040 --> 12:27.008
than contribute to this problem.

12:27.042 --> 12:28.743
Yeah, if everyone who ever
threw a rock at a cop

12:28.777 --> 12:30.511
could wear this badge for one day,

12:30.546 --> 12:32.680
they'd understand it's a war out there.

12:32.705 --> 12:34.849
And the enemies dress
the same as civilians.

12:34.883 --> 12:37.407
Oh, be honest, man.
The enemies dress like us, too.

12:37.953 --> 12:39.721
And I'm not talking about
the Intelligence Unit.

12:39.755 --> 12:41.823
<i>♪ </i>

12:41.857 --> 12:43.391
Well, you wanna know a secret?

12:43.425 --> 12:44.826
<i>♪ </i>

12:44.860 --> 12:46.828
I'm still a black man
under these clothes.

12:46.862 --> 12:48.930
[LAUGHS]

12:48.964 --> 12:52.033
Yeah, but if I get gunned down,
I'm just a dead cop.

12:52.067 --> 12:54.382
It's the risk I signed up for.

12:55.437 --> 12:56.838
Solutions gotta start somewhere.

12:56.872 --> 12:58.386
Yeah, it does.

12:58.741 --> 13:00.908
And today, I am grateful
that you stopped me.

13:00.943 --> 13:05.894
But tomorrow, we could be those
guys lying dead in the street.

13:06.186 --> 13:07.949
Or the ones throwing the rocks.

13:07.983 --> 13:10.551
<i>♪ </i>

13:10.586 --> 13:12.053
Or the ones throwing the rocks.

13:12.087 --> 13:16.524
<i>♪ </i>

13:17.826 --> 13:20.428
At least you don't have a
conscience weighing you down.

13:21.930 --> 13:24.799
You are unburdened by common sense.

13:24.833 --> 13:26.434
What happened to Nava's notebook?

13:26.468 --> 13:28.536
It was there in the apartment
when I left you.

13:28.570 --> 13:29.965
But once the warrant was served...

13:29.999 --> 13:31.606
You made the mistake of
arresting Bennett.

13:31.640 --> 13:32.774
That's what happened.

13:33.443 --> 13:35.009
And that's after Ramsey had
proceeded with the cartel

13:35.034 --> 13:36.511
and made them understand the foolishness

13:36.536 --> 13:37.945
in calling in hits on police officers.

13:37.970 --> 13:39.580
What, am I supposed to be grateful?

13:39.605 --> 13:42.083
He did that to protect himself, not us.

13:42.597 --> 13:44.452
Oddly on this, he has a code.

13:44.486 --> 13:46.554
<i>♪ </i>

13:46.588 --> 13:48.089
I need you to get me
something to hold Bennett.

13:48.123 --> 13:49.590
No evidence will stick.

13:49.625 --> 13:51.218
Not if you keep destroying it.

13:51.252 --> 13:53.125
Look, you got Bennett for one day.

13:53.159 --> 13:54.462
Congratulations.

13:54.487 --> 13:55.763
But you are not going to take
down Jordan Ramsey

13:55.788 --> 13:56.864
with the clock running.

13:57.254 --> 13:58.463
He's playing a different game.

13:58.488 --> 13:59.901
You wanted me to break the blue wall.

14:00.255 --> 14:01.936
I bulldozed it. Now I need your help.

14:01.970 --> 14:03.219
I didn't tell you to do that.

14:03.253 --> 14:05.573
You practically dared me.

14:05.607 --> 14:08.476
Feeding me information,
hoping that I use it.

14:08.510 --> 14:10.845
Regretting how it all went wrong.

14:10.879 --> 14:12.914
Wanting to look in the mirror again?

14:12.948 --> 14:14.782
<i>♪ </i>

14:14.817 --> 14:15.950
Well, this is it.

14:15.984 --> 14:17.852
We're here.

14:17.886 --> 14:19.921
Ten minutes with the son of a kingpin.

14:19.955 --> 14:21.469
That's all I'm asking.

14:21.494 --> 14:23.118
Matt, the orders came down
from up on high.

14:23.143 --> 14:25.827
Nobody talks to Enrique Ortiz,
not even me.

14:25.861 --> 14:27.369
The DEA is taking the lead.

14:27.394 --> 14:31.132
Enrique Ortiz sent
an assassin against my crew.

14:31.166 --> 14:32.934
I gotta chase this down!

14:32.968 --> 14:35.803
Matt, I wish I didn't occupy
the rung of a very tall ladder,

14:35.838 --> 14:36.971
but I can't change that.

14:37.005 --> 14:39.140
Not with that attitude, you can't.

14:39.174 --> 14:41.642
Yeah, I wish I could tell you
that Enrique Ortiz's

14:41.677 --> 14:43.511
only known contact in New York
was a lawyer

14:43.545 --> 14:45.034
named Dustin Hayworth.

14:45.714 --> 14:47.648
It's too bad you can't.

14:47.683 --> 14:49.584
Like I said, I wish I could have helped.

14:52.125 --> 14:53.855
Hey, there she is.

14:53.889 --> 14:55.005
Well, it's official.

14:55.030 --> 14:56.659
We've got a real life American hero

14:56.684 --> 14:58.659
in our interrogation room.

14:58.694 --> 15:01.592
With no bust to play.

15:01.931 --> 15:02.898
Doesn't matter.

15:02.923 --> 15:03.690
I already got two officers

15:03.732 --> 15:04.811
wanting to shake Bennett's hand.

15:04.836 --> 15:06.525
And when I take him down
for multiple homicides,

15:06.550 --> 15:08.379
- they'll regret that.
- Yeah, you want my advice?

15:08.404 --> 15:09.457
Do I have an option?

15:09.482 --> 15:10.705
Work this case with your head down.

15:10.730 --> 15:13.176
Do not try to fight this story.
They're already too far ahead.

15:13.201 --> 15:15.710
- And the clock is ticking.
- They went after my kid, Verco.

15:15.744 --> 15:17.712
The story's not over.

15:17.746 --> 15:20.715
And the city loves a good twist.

15:20.749 --> 15:21.983
You got fan mail?

15:22.017 --> 15:26.554
<i>♪ </i>

15:26.588 --> 15:27.989
No leads sounds a little harsh.

15:28.023 --> 15:29.370
You know this case?

15:29.395 --> 15:30.658
I mean, I've seen the file, yeah.

15:30.692 --> 15:33.561
There are no leads, but still it sounds

15:33.595 --> 15:34.562
a little harsh.

15:34.596 --> 15:35.863
This was on my block.

15:35.898 --> 15:39.700
<i>♪ </i>

15:39.735 --> 15:40.902
"Healed yet?"

15:40.960 --> 15:43.004
It must be a prank from
the guys downstairs, right?

15:43.038 --> 15:45.006
"It was him or you."

15:45.040 --> 15:45.973
<i>♪ </i>

15:46.387 --> 15:48.709
We thought Enrique Ortiz
only sent one sicario.

15:48.744 --> 15:49.777
<i>♪ </i>

15:49.812 --> 15:51.078
Maybe it was two.

15:51.113 --> 15:52.880
Sounds like somebody saved your life.

15:52.915 --> 15:55.883
<i>♪ </i>

15:55.918 --> 15:58.753
Any idea who that might be?
Hey, Detective!

15:58.755 --> 16:01.264
♪

16:01.537 --> 16:03.237
It's him.

16:03.544 --> 16:05.199
He didn't even bother
to disguise his handwriting.

16:05.224 --> 16:06.650
Detective Santos, this isn't a good time.

16:06.675 --> 16:07.958
My apologies.

16:07.983 --> 16:09.253
When would be the most convenient time

16:09.278 --> 16:11.175
for my psychotic stalker
to show up again?

16:11.200 --> 16:13.276
Ideally when someone else
is around to see him.

16:13.311 --> 16:14.557
Look.

16:15.666 --> 16:17.858
I tried to let it go. Okay, I did.

16:17.892 --> 16:20.053
And maybe it wasn't him all along,

16:20.078 --> 16:23.013
but I know that this is him.

16:23.048 --> 16:25.015
He said he was gonna heal me.

16:26.184 --> 16:28.018
I never told anybody that.

16:32.023 --> 16:33.257
This happened on your block?

16:33.291 --> 16:34.858
Yesterday.

16:34.883 --> 16:36.660
I didn't see anything,
and they don't have any leads.

16:36.685 --> 16:38.094
Okay, well, I'm gonna need for you

16:38.119 --> 16:39.229
to fill out a witness statement.

16:39.254 --> 16:41.365
Can we just skip to the part
where you start trusting me

16:41.390 --> 16:42.966
and send this to forensics?

16:42.991 --> 16:44.595
A lot of steps between here
and there, Detective.

16:44.620 --> 16:46.170
I've earned more than that.

16:49.941 --> 16:52.009
There's been a development.

16:52.043 --> 16:53.877
We are currently pursuing another avenue

16:53.912 --> 16:55.279
of investigation.

16:55.313 --> 16:56.699
What development?

16:56.733 --> 16:59.116
Your only witness retracted her story.

16:59.150 --> 17:00.284
Gina?

17:00.318 --> 17:01.418
She claims that she was coerced

17:01.453 --> 17:04.188
into giving a false statement.

17:04.222 --> 17:05.923
[SIGHS]

17:05.957 --> 17:08.425
She knows better than anybody
how obsessed he is...

17:08.460 --> 17:10.137
how dangerous.

17:10.962 --> 17:12.930
Apparently she feels
that the obsession runs

17:12.964 --> 17:13.931
in the other direction.

17:13.964 --> 17:16.934
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

17:16.968 --> 17:24.007
<i>♪ </i>

17:27.645 --> 17:29.213
Is Dustin Hayward in?

17:29.247 --> 17:30.380
He is, but he's on a call.

17:30.415 --> 17:31.381
- Can I take...
- Thanks.

17:31.416 --> 17:33.217
Um, excuse me.

17:34.419 --> 17:36.286
Dustin Hayward, NYPD.

17:37.322 --> 17:39.089
I knew you'd come.

17:39.124 --> 17:40.924
The times, they move so fast.

17:40.959 --> 17:42.226
You taking a vacation?

17:43.261 --> 17:44.881
Plan A.

17:45.330 --> 17:47.197
But, uh, we're past that now.

17:48.133 --> 17:51.401
It's always hard to find a
good hotel at the last minute.

17:51.436 --> 17:53.237
Me, I'm happy in a sleeping bag.

17:53.271 --> 17:55.339
My wife, she needs all the amenities.

17:55.373 --> 17:56.621
What about you, Carlos?

17:56.656 --> 17:57.975
If I don't have a chocolate on my pillow,

17:58.009 --> 17:59.143
I'm out the door.

17:59.168 --> 18:01.078
I can't say anything.
Please don't make me.

18:01.112 --> 18:03.733
You don't even know what we're asking.

18:04.315 --> 18:06.216
Look, I know what I did. I know.

18:07.352 --> 18:08.452
It was the money.

18:08.486 --> 18:10.354
Things fell apart. I needed cash.

18:10.388 --> 18:12.256
All right, so tell us about Jordan Ramsey

18:12.290 --> 18:14.258
and Enrique Ortiz.

18:14.292 --> 18:15.791
I can't. They'll kill him.

18:15.825 --> 18:17.060
Who?

18:18.029 --> 18:19.496
I can't say anything to you.

18:19.531 --> 18:22.166
<i>♪ </i>

18:22.200 --> 18:23.544
They'll know.

18:24.169 --> 18:26.036
They?

18:26.070 --> 18:28.105
Are they coming here?

18:28.139 --> 18:30.140
Dustin, help me understand.

18:30.175 --> 18:31.844
I never had a choice.

18:32.410 --> 18:33.610
We can protect you.

18:33.645 --> 18:36.280
<i>♪ </i>

18:36.314 --> 18:39.616
Nothing can protect me now.

18:39.651 --> 18:41.118
<i>♪ </i>

18:41.152 --> 18:42.386
BOTH: No!

18:42.420 --> 18:43.620
<i>♪ </i>

18:43.655 --> 18:45.122
[THUDS]

18:45.156 --> 18:47.591
- [CAR ALARM WAILS]
- [SCREAMING]

18:49.327 --> 18:50.994
- Somebody help!
- Call 911!

18:54.332 --> 18:56.300
Gina! It's me.

18:56.334 --> 18:57.501
Open up.

19:00.371 --> 19:01.505
Gina?

19:01.539 --> 19:03.540
<i>♪ </i>

19:03.575 --> 19:05.008
[KNOCKING]

19:05.043 --> 19:06.076
Gina.

19:06.110 --> 19:06.977
<i>♪ </i>

19:07.011 --> 19:09.079
If you're in there, I just wanna talk.

19:09.113 --> 19:10.901
[CRYING]

19:10.935 --> 19:12.482
Can we do that?

19:12.517 --> 19:16.553
<i>♪ </i>

19:16.588 --> 19:19.325
[KNOCKING]

19:19.326 --> 19:20.871
Gina.

19:21.895 --> 19:24.263
Look, I need your help. Please.

19:24.298 --> 19:27.800
<i>♪ </i>

19:27.835 --> 19:28.968
Gina, are you there?

19:29.003 --> 19:34.941
<i>♪ </i>

19:34.975 --> 19:39.045
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

19:39.079 --> 19:40.279
Yeah.

19:40.314 --> 19:42.181
<i>♪ </i>

19:42.216 --> 19:43.950
What? When?

19:43.984 --> 19:45.872
<i>♪ </i>

19:45.906 --> 19:47.020
I'm on my way.

19:47.054 --> 19:50.223
<i>♪ </i>

19:50.257 --> 19:51.224
[BEEPING]

19:51.258 --> 19:54.894
<i>♪ </i>

19:54.928 --> 19:55.895
[SIGHS]

19:55.929 --> 19:58.031
<i>♪ </i>

19:58.065 --> 20:00.299
She's gone.

20:00.334 --> 20:01.467
[CRYING]

20:01.502 --> 20:03.069
Harlee played her part.

20:03.103 --> 20:05.338
<i>♪ </i>

20:05.372 --> 20:08.841
Now we have ours. The question is,

20:08.876 --> 20:12.845
are we strong enough
to do what's necessary?

20:12.880 --> 20:15.072
[CRYING]

20:17.918 --> 20:20.219
The knot only gets tighter
the more you struggle.

20:20.254 --> 20:21.988
I told you that.

20:22.022 --> 20:23.706
You don't listen.

20:24.111 --> 20:25.812
I listened. Hey, hey, listen to me.

20:25.837 --> 20:28.203
I listened. I tried to understand.

20:28.228 --> 20:30.163
I told you where this was gonna lead.

20:30.197 --> 20:34.100
And I told you that I didn't
have a choice.

20:34.134 --> 20:35.935
Because she took it away from me.

20:35.969 --> 20:38.371
<i>♪ </i>

20:38.405 --> 20:39.872
[CRYING]

20:39.907 --> 20:43.276
Now, debt needs to be paid.

20:43.310 --> 20:45.211
<i>♪ </i>

20:45.245 --> 20:50.116
[CRYING]

20:50.150 --> 20:52.185
I know, I know, I know.

20:52.219 --> 20:54.528
I know you lost a lot.

20:55.489 --> 20:57.198
You lost everything.

20:58.058 --> 20:59.292
I know.

20:59.326 --> 21:00.426
What?

21:00.461 --> 21:02.929
[CRYING]

21:05.332 --> 21:06.933
Cut her loose.

21:06.967 --> 21:11.204
<i>♪ </i>

21:16.973 --> 21:19.599
Tenth floor windows aren't easy to open.

21:19.624 --> 21:21.113
Did you know that, Lieutenant?

21:21.596 --> 21:23.897
Sounds like a question for the architect.

21:23.922 --> 21:25.022
Indulge me.

21:25.047 --> 21:27.482
Being cute's not gonna
change what happened.

21:27.516 --> 21:29.795
Why were you up there to see Mr. Hayward?

21:29.829 --> 21:32.126
His assistant said you barged
in without an appointment.

21:32.151 --> 21:34.568
I'm running an investigation.

21:35.588 --> 21:38.523
Looks like somebody forgot his cape.

21:38.558 --> 21:39.924
What am I looking at?

21:39.949 --> 21:42.394
He lost an argument with gravity.

21:42.428 --> 21:43.476
Who started it?

21:43.510 --> 21:44.529
He did.

21:44.564 --> 21:46.131
This poor bastard was a wreck

21:46.165 --> 21:47.732
the second we walked in the door.

21:47.767 --> 21:49.668
How's our poor bastard holding up?

21:49.702 --> 21:52.304
Same as always. No way to know.

21:54.273 --> 21:55.740
You good, boss?

21:55.775 --> 21:57.709
Better than Mr. Hayward.

21:57.743 --> 21:59.244
Thought we were gonna wait eight hours

21:59.278 --> 22:00.378
till we tried it your way.

22:02.348 --> 22:04.149
Sorry.

22:04.183 --> 22:05.383
Look, did he say anything
before he jumped?

22:05.418 --> 22:06.651
Anything about intelligence?

22:06.676 --> 22:10.855
Just talked about his family
and how he wanted them safe.

22:11.357 --> 22:12.724
Ramsey and the Riohacha cartel?

22:12.758 --> 22:14.559
Yeah, and that's what we have to prove.

22:14.594 --> 22:17.562
We have to find out what
pancake man here...

22:17.597 --> 22:19.664
what he was doing for Ramsey.

22:19.699 --> 22:22.667
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

22:22.702 --> 22:24.436
We gotta search that office.

22:24.470 --> 22:26.538
I tried. They got the whole floor sealed.

22:26.563 --> 22:27.672
They won't let anybody up.

22:27.697 --> 22:28.607
<i>♪ </i>

22:28.641 --> 22:30.375
So we sneak in later?

22:30.409 --> 22:31.710
What, a Breaking and Entering?

22:31.744 --> 22:33.221
- [PHONE CHIRPS]
- That's not cutting corners?

22:33.255 --> 22:36.181
<i>♪ </i>

22:36.215 --> 22:37.549
What?

22:37.583 --> 22:39.251
I'm working a theory.

22:39.285 --> 22:42.396
<i>♪ </i>

22:42.430 --> 22:44.389
Jumping out a window.

22:44.423 --> 22:45.690
That seems like a fitting end

22:45.725 --> 22:48.460
to the end of my tenure with this crew.

22:48.494 --> 22:51.630
You'll go ride off into the sunset, Tess.

22:51.664 --> 22:52.697
Are you kidding me?

22:52.732 --> 22:54.299
I've lost my marriage,

22:54.333 --> 22:55.467
I have been shot,

22:55.501 --> 22:57.569
then operated on by Espada Nightingale,

22:57.603 --> 22:59.471
I have been lied to, demoted,

22:59.505 --> 23:00.772
aced out of a payday

23:00.797 --> 23:03.608
and then, oh, I was called out
of my first date in forever

23:03.643 --> 23:05.810
to torture a hit woman in a shower.

23:05.845 --> 23:07.546
Taking a concrete plunge seems like

23:07.580 --> 23:09.814
the only logical next step for me, Tufo.

23:09.849 --> 23:12.651
Yeah, let's work on that
whole glass half full thing.

23:12.685 --> 23:13.752
- Yeah?
- [SIGHS]

23:13.777 --> 23:15.520
God, now we have to spend half our shifts

23:15.545 --> 23:17.222
doing drive by safety checks.

23:17.247 --> 23:19.558
Everyone's circling the wagons
to save Harlee's ass.

23:19.592 --> 23:20.643
She made her choice.

23:20.668 --> 23:21.793
And we can make a different one.

23:21.818 --> 23:24.262
Yeah, the intelligence unit
tried to kill my brother.

23:24.287 --> 23:26.972
Any choice that involves
taking them down, I'm all in.

23:27.667 --> 23:29.058
Wait, you had a date?

23:29.769 --> 23:31.503
What, no collars, ladies?

23:31.537 --> 23:33.505
That ain't like the street crimes unit.

23:33.539 --> 23:35.407
They're having trouble finding
someone to rough up.

23:35.441 --> 23:37.101
Frame another cop.

23:37.135 --> 23:38.677
Stats are stats, right?

23:38.711 --> 23:40.779
Oh, I'm happy to find someone
to rough up.

23:40.813 --> 23:42.069
You're about to volunteer.

23:42.103 --> 23:43.315
Hey, no, I understand.

23:43.349 --> 23:44.783
Why put yourselves on the line?

23:44.817 --> 23:46.133
That's what brothers are for.

23:46.167 --> 23:47.352
What was that?

23:47.386 --> 23:48.446
No, I think it's smart.

23:48.480 --> 23:50.422
You send in that ex-con brother of yours,

23:50.456 --> 23:51.423
you get the paycheck,

23:51.457 --> 23:53.258
parolee gets a cracked skull.

23:53.993 --> 23:55.527
Oh, no. Tufo, Tufo.

23:55.561 --> 23:57.462
Not worth it, man.

23:57.496 --> 23:58.663
Wallace is twice the man you are!

23:58.698 --> 23:59.664
- Come on!
- Get off!

23:59.699 --> 24:00.832
You son of a bitch!

24:00.857 --> 24:02.767
I may be a son of a bitch,
but I'm no traitor!

24:02.802 --> 24:04.302
Hey, knock it off!

24:04.337 --> 24:05.537
You put a leash on that attack dog, Tess!

24:05.571 --> 24:06.543
Quiet!

24:06.568 --> 24:08.360
Is this what we want the
public to see from the NYPD?

24:08.385 --> 24:09.608
Now what is this?

24:09.633 --> 24:10.775
It's a bit of a disagreement.

24:11.124 --> 24:13.678
I say cops don't turn on other cops.

24:13.713 --> 24:15.814
They do when the cop has
committed multiple homicides.

24:15.848 --> 24:17.021
All right, that's it.

24:17.046 --> 24:19.284
The two of you go home and get right.

24:19.318 --> 24:21.853
'Cause I'm filing conduct
reports on both your asses.

24:23.656 --> 24:26.691
[CALM MUSIC PLAYING]

24:26.726 --> 24:30.795
♪

24:30.830 --> 24:31.863
What are you drinking?

24:31.897 --> 24:34.499
♪

24:34.533 --> 24:35.567
Same as you.

24:35.601 --> 24:39.304
♪

24:39.338 --> 24:40.739
Left my gun in my car.

24:40.773 --> 24:42.574
I'm not carrying.

24:42.608 --> 24:44.709
We're more evolved animals, I think.

24:44.744 --> 24:46.969
No, we're cavemen.

24:47.613 --> 24:50.715
We worship the shadows on the wall.

24:50.750 --> 24:52.256
Long day?

24:52.291 --> 24:53.718
I've had longer.

24:53.753 --> 24:56.073
♪

24:56.107 --> 24:57.722
He was my detective.

24:57.757 --> 24:59.891
I know. David Saperstein.

24:59.925 --> 25:01.826
I read the report. Four story fall.

25:01.861 --> 25:04.829
♪

25:04.864 --> 25:06.364
I pushed him.

25:06.399 --> 25:09.601
♪

25:09.635 --> 25:12.076
Funny what our hands are
capable of, isn't it?

25:12.077 --> 25:13.311
You think that you know them.

25:13.345 --> 25:15.313
♪

25:15.347 --> 25:18.149
I had to do it myself.

25:18.183 --> 25:22.338
If it had to be done, it was gonna be me.

25:23.088 --> 25:24.757
Noble sentiment.

25:25.190 --> 25:27.058
But once you've led a platoon
into an ambush

25:27.092 --> 25:29.594
and watched men cut down
because of your decisions,

25:29.628 --> 25:31.329
you'd let it go.

25:31.363 --> 25:33.331
Is that why you didn't kill Parker?

25:33.365 --> 25:35.299
♪

25:35.334 --> 25:36.501
I couldn't do it.

25:36.535 --> 25:38.069
That make me a coward?

25:38.094 --> 25:41.239
I think you were probably
a coward way before that.

25:41.273 --> 25:42.573
[LAUGHS]

25:42.608 --> 25:44.575
Oh. [LAUGHS]

25:47.821 --> 25:49.347
So, what am I doing here, Lieutenant?

25:49.381 --> 25:52.150
♪

25:52.184 --> 25:54.185
Your man Bennett won't talk.

25:54.219 --> 25:58.356
He may be a homicidal maniac,
but he's loyal.

25:58.390 --> 26:00.291
I could have told you that
before you put him in cuffs.

26:00.325 --> 26:02.493
I got a deal for you.

26:02.528 --> 26:05.496
Give us a charge that we
could hang on him.

26:05.531 --> 26:09.167
He pleads out, my crew gets safe,

26:09.201 --> 26:11.502
and we make it out alive.

26:11.537 --> 26:13.972
Are you asking me to leave a man behind?

26:14.406 --> 26:15.373
You'd never do that.

26:15.407 --> 26:17.308
I have higher standards.

26:17.342 --> 26:19.144
What you have...

26:19.578 --> 26:21.179
Is 15 more hours.

26:21.213 --> 26:23.214
I can't leave Bennett in custody.
He's a hero now.

26:23.248 --> 26:24.115
[BLOWS AIR]

26:24.140 --> 26:26.717
A hero's a villain with a backstory.

26:26.752 --> 26:28.152
That's true.

26:28.177 --> 26:30.388
I've broken laws I had a hand in writing.

26:30.422 --> 26:31.530
Neglected my second wife.

26:31.564 --> 26:34.034
Haven't spoken to my kids in ten years.

26:34.726 --> 26:37.528
But at least they're still breathing.

26:37.563 --> 26:38.529
You?

26:38.564 --> 26:44.135
♪

26:44.169 --> 26:45.570
You're the angel of death.

26:45.604 --> 26:48.573
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

26:48.607 --> 26:55.646
<i>♪ </i>

27:03.622 --> 27:05.156
What are we doing here?

27:05.190 --> 27:07.025
Ramsey needs something in that office.

27:07.726 --> 27:09.227
Something to keep Bennett in custody?

27:09.261 --> 27:10.361
All I know is it's important.

27:10.386 --> 27:13.397
The crime scene's gonna be left
unattended in ten minutes.

27:14.466 --> 27:16.601
For your guys to make an appearance.

27:16.635 --> 27:18.536
We have a narrow window.

27:19.605 --> 27:21.439
Do you know why this guy jumped?

27:21.473 --> 27:23.708
Maybe when we get up there,
we'll see the appeal.

27:26.144 --> 27:27.278
[CAR ALARM CHIRPS]

27:27.312 --> 27:30.281
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

27:30.315 --> 27:37.355
<i>♪ </i>

27:59.361 --> 28:00.816
<i>Intel's good so far.</i>

28:00.841 --> 28:02.180
Thank you.

28:02.214 --> 28:03.610
- Gloves?
- Got my own.

28:03.644 --> 28:08.782
<i>♪ </i>

28:08.816 --> 28:10.650
How'd this guy get on your boss' radar?

28:10.685 --> 28:13.175
Did some legal work for Enrique Ortiz.

28:13.854 --> 28:15.422
How'd he get on Ramsey's?

28:15.456 --> 28:16.957
I'd guess the same.

28:16.991 --> 28:19.993
Cartel money is a road map right to him.

28:20.027 --> 28:21.995
That's a sound theory.

28:22.029 --> 28:24.764
Poor guy was more scared
to talk than he was to die.

28:24.799 --> 28:27.834
<i>♪ </i>

28:27.868 --> 28:30.937
Cleaned out his desk pretty thoroughly.

28:30.972 --> 28:32.375
Had time to prepare.

28:32.409 --> 28:35.208
<i>♪ </i>

28:35.243 --> 28:37.322
Doesn't sound like he had
much of a choice.

28:37.356 --> 28:40.447
<i>♪ </i>

28:40.481 --> 28:42.195
What'd be going through your head...

28:42.229 --> 28:44.351
<i>♪ </i>

28:44.385 --> 28:46.333
If you knew it was coming?

28:46.854 --> 28:48.955
Well, I'd be wishing I hadn't
wasted so much time

28:48.990 --> 28:50.223
matching my socks.

28:50.258 --> 28:53.493
<i>♪ </i>

28:53.527 --> 28:55.092
My wife.

28:55.863 --> 28:57.003
What was that?

28:57.037 --> 28:58.595
If I were him...

28:59.066 --> 29:01.334
If I had a wife,
I'd be thinking about her.

29:01.369 --> 29:04.504
My kids. I'd want them to
know why this happened.

29:04.538 --> 29:05.810
I'd try to communicate something.

29:05.844 --> 29:07.340
What... what did he say to your friends?

29:07.375 --> 29:10.010
Just that they'd know if he talked.

29:10.044 --> 29:11.511
That his family was in danger.

29:11.545 --> 29:13.380
<i>♪ </i>

29:13.414 --> 29:15.015
He gave Espada a photo of them.

29:15.049 --> 29:20.720
<i>♪ </i>

29:20.755 --> 29:21.721
This photo?

29:21.756 --> 29:28.795
<i>♪ </i>

29:33.868 --> 29:36.036
Fed Prac Digest Volume Four.

29:36.070 --> 29:37.871
<i>♪ </i>

29:37.905 --> 29:39.539
Federal Practice.

29:39.573 --> 29:41.007
It's a book.

29:41.042 --> 29:43.276
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

29:43.311 --> 29:45.512
Circled this school
three times in twenty minutes.

29:45.546 --> 29:46.880
You feel like filling me in?

29:48.282 --> 29:50.050
That's information beyond your pay grade.

29:50.084 --> 29:52.385
Pretty sure we're wearing
the same uniform.

29:52.420 --> 29:54.421
Even if one of us doesn't respect it.

29:54.455 --> 29:56.423
You're about 30 seconds from
getting kicked out of this car.

29:56.457 --> 29:57.824
It's my car.

29:57.849 --> 30:00.393
You're in it 'cause your crazy
partner got his ass sent home.

30:00.428 --> 30:02.395
Dragged my partner with him.

30:02.430 --> 30:03.463
[SIGHS]

30:03.497 --> 30:05.465
Will food shut you up?

30:05.499 --> 30:07.039
Worth a shot.

30:07.802 --> 30:09.069
Volume four.

30:09.103 --> 30:10.070
Got it.

30:10.104 --> 30:13.073
<i>♪ </i>

30:13.107 --> 30:14.441
Treasure map?

30:14.475 --> 30:17.444
It's a formation document
for an offshore LLC.

30:17.478 --> 30:19.045
Magnolia Limited.

30:19.080 --> 30:20.780
<i>♪ </i>

30:20.815 --> 30:22.082
Good way to stay anonymous.

30:22.116 --> 30:23.917
<i>♪ </i>

30:23.951 --> 30:26.266
This isn't anonymous.

30:27.021 --> 30:28.769
It's Ramsey.

30:29.357 --> 30:30.525
Are you sure?

30:30.550 --> 30:32.959
Magnolia was his last operation overseas.

30:32.993 --> 30:35.595
It... it went badly.
He lost a lot of men.

30:35.629 --> 30:37.097
He's... he's never been able
to let it go.

30:37.131 --> 30:38.965
I thought you said
he didn't confide in you.

30:38.999 --> 30:40.467
I used to be the Golden Boy.

30:40.501 --> 30:43.336
<i>♪ </i>

30:43.371 --> 30:44.804
It's a purchase agreement

30:44.839 --> 30:46.106
for a property in Red Hook.

30:46.140 --> 30:48.341
A bonded warehouse.

30:48.376 --> 30:49.943
Bonded?

30:49.977 --> 30:51.478
They have lax custom requirements

30:51.512 --> 30:53.446
and sporadic oversight.

30:53.481 --> 30:55.148
<i>♪ </i>

30:55.182 --> 30:56.672
Look.

30:57.118 --> 30:58.485
It opens onto the river.

30:58.519 --> 30:59.819
[BELL DINGS]

30:59.854 --> 31:01.306
Come on. Leave the paper.

31:01.340 --> 31:02.489
Get the address.

31:02.523 --> 31:05.158
<i>♪ </i>

31:05.192 --> 31:06.159
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

31:06.193 --> 31:09.162
<i>♪ </i>

31:09.196 --> 31:11.531
Come on. Too late.

31:11.565 --> 31:12.643
Over here.

31:12.677 --> 31:19.839
<i>♪ </i>

31:21.509 --> 31:23.977
Think this place is haunted yet?

31:24.011 --> 31:25.478
He didn't die until after he landed.

31:25.513 --> 31:27.113
<i>♪ </i>

31:27.148 --> 31:29.616
I'm not seeing anything
labeled Ramsey or Magnolia.

31:29.650 --> 31:30.984
It wouldn't be labeled.

31:31.009 --> 31:32.886
All that matter is Matt Wozniak
didn't come away

31:32.920 --> 31:34.020
with any leads.

31:34.054 --> 31:35.488
Well, there's nothing here.

31:35.523 --> 31:37.891
Hayward probably shredded them.

31:37.925 --> 31:39.392
Maybe packed them away.

31:39.427 --> 31:42.162
<i>♪ </i>

31:42.196 --> 31:43.997
Wait.

31:44.031 --> 31:46.499
This book is upside down.

31:46.534 --> 31:49.002
<i>♪ </i>

31:49.036 --> 31:50.726
This is it.

31:51.205 --> 31:52.906
Good effort, Mr. Hayworth.

31:52.940 --> 31:54.474
Let's go.

31:54.508 --> 31:56.976
Ramsey wants us there to
chaperone tonight's operation.

31:57.011 --> 32:02.482
<i>♪ </i>

32:02.516 --> 32:04.083
Tonight's operation?

32:04.118 --> 32:06.019
<i>♪ </i>

32:06.053 --> 32:07.780
I'll find out.

32:07.815 --> 32:12.392
<i>♪ </i>

32:16.530 --> 32:18.198
I thought I heard the door.

32:18.232 --> 32:19.599
What are you doing home?

32:19.633 --> 32:21.034
I wanted to see you.

32:21.068 --> 32:23.203
You talking to me or Jack Daniels?

32:23.237 --> 32:24.537
Both.

32:26.907 --> 32:28.541
He's gonna have to keep you occupied,

32:28.576 --> 32:32.011
because I have a...
a fundraiser to go to.

32:32.046 --> 32:33.012
St. Francis?

32:33.047 --> 32:34.180
[LAUGHS]

32:34.215 --> 32:35.915
Yeah, the one that you got out of

32:35.950 --> 32:37.116
by saying that you had to work?

32:37.151 --> 32:39.519
Yeah, I'm a slippery fish.

32:43.457 --> 32:45.425
- See you later.
- Okay.

32:45.993 --> 32:48.094
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN, CLOSES]

32:51.432 --> 32:53.199
<i>It's barely a scratch.</i>

32:53.234 --> 32:54.807
<i>I already told you I'd pay for it.</i>

32:54.842 --> 32:56.583
What'd you say?

32:57.505 --> 32:59.939
<i>I don't want you hanging out
with that crowd!</i>

32:59.974 --> 33:01.541
<i>You're better than them!</i>

33:01.575 --> 33:03.076
<i>I'm not a little girl anymore.</i>

33:03.110 --> 33:04.711
<i>Let me live my life.</i>

33:04.745 --> 33:06.579
<i>Fine, fine. You live your life.</i>

33:06.614 --> 33:08.481
<i>You see where you end up.</i>

33:08.516 --> 33:10.216
<i>What do you care?</i>

33:10.251 --> 33:12.085
<i>You're never here.</i>

33:12.119 --> 33:13.186
<i>I could be drowning,</i>

33:13.211 --> 33:14.687
<i>and you'd call me from your office</i>

33:14.712 --> 33:16.556
<i>yelling at me to learn to swim.</i>

33:16.581 --> 33:18.191
<i>And you know what would happen?</i>

33:18.216 --> 33:20.093
<i>You'd sink!</i>

33:20.127 --> 33:22.128
<i>Right to the bottom!</i>

33:22.162 --> 33:24.163
<i>♪ </i>

33:24.198 --> 33:25.765
<i>[DOOR OPENS]</i>

33:25.799 --> 33:32.972
<i>♪ </i>

34:12.246 --> 34:14.112
Sorry, Beauty.

34:14.148 --> 34:16.315
<i>♪ </i>

34:16.350 --> 34:18.915
I'm sorry that I let you drown.

34:19.853 --> 34:22.188
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

34:24.525 --> 34:27.327
Boss, 14 hours left on Bennett.

34:27.360 --> 34:29.027
Why aren't you answering your phone?

34:29.063 --> 34:30.228
I didn't hear it ringing.

34:30.264 --> 34:32.065
Your jumper left us a lead.

34:32.099 --> 34:33.032
On the pavement?

34:33.056 --> 34:34.467
Ramsey's bringing in another shipment.

34:34.501 --> 34:36.369
A shipment of what?

34:36.402 --> 34:38.170
Something he doesn't want customs to see.

34:38.205 --> 34:39.539
I'll brief you on the way.

34:45.779 --> 34:53.052
<i>♪ </i>

35:07.195 --> 35:09.200
Just how you wanna be
spending your day off, huh?

35:09.234 --> 35:10.515
Avenging my brother's assault

35:10.540 --> 35:12.006
beats cereal on the couch.

35:12.040 --> 35:13.673
Ah, come on. Just admit it.

35:13.707 --> 35:15.189
You missed us.

35:15.223 --> 35:16.972
So Harlee, how sure are we
that your man inside

35:17.007 --> 35:19.060
isn't Ramsey's man inside?

35:19.095 --> 35:20.186
That's what the vests are for.

35:20.187 --> 35:22.098
Whatever it is is gonna lead
us back to Intelligence?

35:22.123 --> 35:23.591
Ramsey owns this warehouse.

35:23.625 --> 35:26.093
Anything we seize is potential evidence.

35:26.127 --> 35:28.061
Okay, but... but before
we go any further,

35:28.095 --> 35:29.441
don't you think we should maybe, like,

35:29.475 --> 35:31.465
I don't know, take a vote or something?

35:31.499 --> 35:33.467
- A vote?
- Yeah.

35:33.909 --> 35:35.210
I don't remember deciding to start a war

35:35.244 --> 35:36.281
with the Intelligence Unit

35:36.315 --> 35:37.979
and alienate the entire police force.

35:38.014 --> 35:40.215
The war didn't wait for you to decide.

35:40.249 --> 35:41.816
It's here.

35:41.851 --> 35:42.884
We gotta stop it now.

35:42.918 --> 35:45.186
I'm just saying,
maybe if we had taken a vote,

35:45.221 --> 35:46.755
none of this would have happened.

35:46.789 --> 35:48.490
Fine, every detective gets one vote.

35:48.524 --> 35:49.824
Lieutenant gets five.

35:49.859 --> 35:51.159
The ayes have it.

35:51.193 --> 35:53.828
Tufo, James Madison, myself,

35:53.863 --> 35:55.063
we're gonna go around the side.

35:55.097 --> 35:56.197
Look, I don't know about anyone else,

35:56.232 --> 35:57.572
but I'm feeling backup on this.

35:58.067 --> 35:59.543
No, we need to keep this off the grid.

35:59.570 --> 36:00.969
Intelligence knows your Google history.

36:00.994 --> 36:02.203
You two go in the back.

36:02.228 --> 36:03.578
We're gonna make enough an impression

36:03.603 --> 36:06.007
that whoever's back there
will never notice you.

36:06.042 --> 36:07.208
- Loman.
- Yeah.

36:07.243 --> 36:08.243
Let's go make a scene.

36:08.277 --> 36:09.244
[GUN COCKS]

36:09.278 --> 36:12.247
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

36:12.281 --> 36:19.487
<i>♪ </i>

36:33.002 --> 36:36.604
The party doesn't seem to be
very well attended.

36:36.639 --> 36:38.540
I'm not loving this feeling.

36:38.574 --> 36:41.109
<i>♪ </i>

36:41.143 --> 36:43.244
All right, let's find the water.

36:43.279 --> 36:50.285
<i>♪ </i>

37:26.188 --> 37:27.355
6:10.

37:27.389 --> 37:29.522
Harlee said six.

37:30.192 --> 37:32.026
This isn't right.

37:32.061 --> 37:33.985
These guys are precise.

37:34.630 --> 37:36.297
Well, we're here.

37:36.332 --> 37:39.167
Maybe this is precisely what they wanted.

37:39.201 --> 37:41.993
<i>♪ </i>

37:43.639 --> 37:44.939
Not promising.

37:44.974 --> 37:46.107
<i>Harlee, you there?</i>

37:46.142 --> 37:47.675
<i>♪ </i>

37:47.710 --> 37:49.010
Go ahead.

37:49.044 --> 37:50.612
We found the dock. No sign of a shipment.

37:50.646 --> 37:53.114
<i>How solid are you on this intel?</i>

37:53.149 --> 37:55.383
No sign of anything?

37:55.417 --> 37:57.018
Yo, let's get the hell out of here.

37:57.052 --> 37:58.052
This doesn't feel right.

37:58.087 --> 37:59.354
Woz says we need to go.

37:59.388 --> 38:01.590
<i>No!</i> We only have Bennett
for a few more hours.

38:01.625 --> 38:03.176
This is our shot.

38:03.210 --> 38:06.394
[DISTANT CREAKING]

38:06.428 --> 38:08.329
Harlee, I heard something.

38:08.364 --> 38:10.031
[PHONE VIBRATES]

38:10.065 --> 38:11.399
<i>♪ </i>

38:11.433 --> 38:12.732
What is it?

38:13.795 --> 38:15.429
We gotta move.

38:15.738 --> 38:19.007
[GUNFIRE]

38:19.041 --> 38:21.209
Harlee! Harlee, you there?

38:21.243 --> 38:24.212
[GUNFIRE]

38:24.246 --> 38:26.714
We'll find them. Stay low.

38:26.749 --> 38:30.218
[GUNFIRE]

38:30.252 --> 38:31.386
[SHOUTS]

38:31.420 --> 38:34.055
[GUNFIRE]

38:34.089 --> 38:36.157
Dispatch, Tango Nine Zero Three.

38:36.192 --> 38:39.060
I've got a 13. Shots fired.

38:39.094 --> 38:41.362
<i>Tango Nine Zero Three,
what's your location?</i>

38:41.397 --> 38:43.231
67 West Street. [GUNFIRE]

38:43.265 --> 38:44.701
Taking rounds!

38:44.736 --> 38:46.434
Requesting immediate backup.

38:46.468 --> 38:49.204
[GUNFIRE]

38:51.607 --> 38:52.674
No.

38:52.708 --> 38:59.714
<i>♪ </i>

39:35.184 --> 39:36.484
Don't flinch.

39:36.518 --> 39:39.754
<i>♪ </i>

39:43.459 --> 39:45.526
So, did you miss this?

39:47.463 --> 39:49.163
Patrol.

39:49.198 --> 39:50.498
I mean, you spent thousands of hours

39:50.532 --> 39:53.468
earning that detective badge, but this?

39:53.502 --> 39:55.470
This is simple right and wrong.

39:55.504 --> 39:58.406
You certainly got that simple part down.

39:59.341 --> 40:02.143
Whatever. Just making conversation.

40:02.177 --> 40:04.445
<i>Attention all units, all units respond.</i>

40:04.480 --> 40:06.314
<i>67 West Street. Shots fired.</i>

40:06.348 --> 40:07.758
<i>Officers on scene.</i>

40:07.793 --> 40:10.118
That's Dockside.
It's about eight blocks away.

40:10.152 --> 40:13.154
[SIRENS WAILING]

40:13.188 --> 40:17.325
<i>♪ </i>

40:17.359 --> 40:19.794
So, what's the plan?

40:19.828 --> 40:22.764
How long you think we can hold
them until backup arrives?

40:22.798 --> 40:25.333
We hold on till we can't.

40:25.367 --> 40:27.468
I didn't see any new
shipment come in, Harlee.

40:27.503 --> 40:29.634
This is the last time we trust
this source of yours.

40:29.668 --> 40:30.983
It's the last time we do anything.

40:31.008 --> 40:33.408
You mind if we get out of
here before you start bitching?

40:33.441 --> 40:34.907
Hey, hey, cavalry's here.

40:34.943 --> 40:36.344
[SIRENS WAILING]

40:36.378 --> 40:37.986
We've gotta hunker down.

40:38.020 --> 40:39.514
<i>Dispatch, can you confirm the call sign</i>

40:39.548 --> 40:41.256
<i>of the officers on scene?</i>

40:41.884 --> 40:44.739
<i>Officer ID, Tango Nine Zero Three.</i>

40:44.773 --> 40:46.040
That's Harlee's number.

40:46.074 --> 40:47.488
What? You sure?

40:47.523 --> 40:49.857
[SIRENS WAILING]

40:49.892 --> 40:51.326
What's he doing?

40:51.360 --> 40:53.194
<i>♪ </i>

40:53.228 --> 40:55.530
Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, they're turning back.

40:55.564 --> 40:56.798
What is this?

40:56.832 --> 40:58.499
<i>♪ </i>

40:58.534 --> 41:00.168
[SIREN CLICKS OFF]

41:00.202 --> 41:01.235
No, no, no, Stone!

41:01.270 --> 41:04.934
Turn this car around right now,
you son of a bitch!

41:04.968 --> 41:06.074
No, they can't leave us!

41:06.108 --> 41:07.809
Yo, somebody radio dispatch!

41:07.843 --> 41:09.742
It's the Blue Wall.

41:10.230 --> 41:12.930
Once you cross it, you're alone.

41:12.964 --> 41:17.385
[GUNFIRE]

41:20.036 --> 41:22.271
Don't do this. These are good people!

41:22.305 --> 41:25.174
And they serve the same city as you.

41:25.208 --> 41:28.177
Stone, come on.

41:28.211 --> 41:30.312
<i>♪ </i>

41:30.347 --> 41:32.348
Turn around, or I swear to God,

41:32.382 --> 41:34.049
I'll shoot you right here.

41:34.084 --> 41:36.394
